[/quote]diaf imo, I have >1 year old autoed accounts that are absolutely clean in terms of offenses.

which is why the action jack system didn’t help detectabilty any

But if you click on something once and it examines it, don’t you think that’s still detectable?

item.dc:creator: @Javacisnotrecognized _^_
item.description:
@Javacisnotrecognized wrote:

Aryan SCAR and ARGA are entirely different things. Aryan was ‘attached’ to the client, and would invoke it’s methods on objects before they were on the screen. As has been mentioned before, SCAR is a color clicker, which I believe is why there are so many of those bitmap functions. ARGA is an … um … thing that you should ask Taios what it is.
